1
00:00:08,119 --> 00:00:11,480
God, I'm exhausted.
-Tough night.

2
00:00:12,720 --> 00:00:15,520
Sorry again for dropping in on you like this.

3
00:00:15,640 --> 00:00:17,840
Chill, chill, bro. You've got other problems.

4
00:00:17,960 --> 00:00:20,080
You can always come and talk. No problem at all.

5
00:00:20,520 --> 00:00:21,960
Just look at the mess you left in the kitchen.

6
00:00:22,040 --> 00:00:24,040
I don't get when you even had time to talk.

7
00:00:24,320 --> 00:00:26,600
You totally wrecked the kitchen.
You went through the fridge,

8
00:00:26,720 --> 00:00:29,760
cleared it out shelf by shelf.
I came in the morning, and the kitchen looked

9
00:00:29,920 --> 00:00:31,560
like Yarkon Park after Mimouna celebrations.

10
00:00:32,080 --> 00:00:33,840
We wanted to tidy up but didn’t want to make noise.

11
00:00:33,920 --> 00:00:35,000
Okay.
-So...

12
00:00:35,080 --> 00:00:37,120
There was a little cake there,
I hope it wasn't saved for anything.

13
00:00:37,680 --> 00:00:38,920
Yeah, it was a bite between—

14
00:00:39,080 --> 00:00:41,200
Great, that's the little one's birthday cake.

15
00:00:43,040 --> 00:00:44,920
Hope it brings good luck.
-Thanks.

16
00:00:45,680 --> 00:00:47,360
I'm really sorry.
-It's okay, bro.

17
00:00:47,840 --> 00:00:49,280
The birthday party was a month ago.

18
00:00:49,360 --> 00:00:50,320
A month?
-A month.

19
00:00:50,840 --> 00:00:52,520
I hope you don't have an "after-party" in your stomach.

20
00:00:53,000 --> 00:00:54,240
Mom, who cried last night?

21
00:00:54,320 --> 00:00:55,960
Evitar Gdasi.

22
00:01:01,920 --> 00:01:04,360
Look at me, look at me and...

23
00:01:12,000 --> 00:01:14,760
Shabbat Shalom.
-Shabbat Shalom.

24
00:01:14,840 --> 00:01:17,520
Where have you been? I was so worried.

25
00:01:17,640 --> 00:01:19,280
Shabbat Shalom. Come on, girls.

26
00:01:19,760 --> 00:01:23,000
Come to Grandpa. Shabbat Shalom, sit down.

27
00:01:23,080 --> 00:01:24,400
Shabbat Shalom, cuties.

28
00:01:25,960 --> 00:01:30,400
Oh, Tzvi, how's it going?
-Shabbat Shalom. You know...

29
00:01:30,760 --> 00:01:32,040
Not really, but I can relate.

30
00:01:33,160 --> 00:01:36,360
Tzvi got a bit tangled up with his future ex.
-Shai...

31
00:01:36,840 --> 00:01:39,440
Just kidding, man, they're in another round of fighting so...

32
00:01:39,960 --> 00:01:41,400
Come to the kitchen, let’s eat some schnitzels.

33
00:01:41,480 --> 00:01:43,760
I get that really lifts the mood.

34
00:01:43,880 --> 00:01:44,720
Good.

35
00:01:48,480 --> 00:01:50,360
So, he cried all night for you?

36
00:01:52,160 --> 00:01:54,080
I know that feeling.

37
00:01:54,960 --> 00:01:57,280
I feel bad for him, I like Tzvi.

38
00:01:57,680 --> 00:01:59,880
I’ll go check they're not making a mess.

39
00:02:02,320 --> 00:02:04,480
Sit down, you shouldn't have agreed.

40
00:02:04,560 --> 00:02:06,240
If he wants to leave, let him go to a hotel.

41
00:02:06,720 --> 00:02:08,600
Ben.
-Okay, okay, the mistake's already made.

42
00:02:08,680 --> 00:02:10,080
So what, is he simmering at your place?
-Yeah.

43
00:02:10,800 --> 00:02:14,040
I don't mind, but I care that he’s putting
all kinds of bugs in Shai's head.

44
00:02:14,120 --> 00:02:17,480
Be a man, don’t be a sucker,
stand your ground. What...

45
00:02:17,560 --> 00:02:19,480
You don't have to worry, Shai won't eat just anything.

46
00:02:19,560 --> 00:02:22,240
No, he actually will. No, I'm joking.

47
00:02:23,520 --> 00:02:26,920
A little. That's not the point, really.
Fighting is totally fine,

48
00:02:27,000 --> 00:02:29,880
it's part of a relationship. But if there's love, Pinchas,

49
00:02:30,280 --> 00:02:34,040
leaving is not an option at all.
-Look, at first Riki and I also...

50
00:02:34,120 --> 00:02:35,720
You know, we used to fight over every little thing.

51
00:02:35,800 --> 00:02:37,600
But then I realized it was pointless.

52
00:02:37,720 --> 00:02:41,760
In the end, she always makes me look guilty
and stupid and I have to apologize,

53
00:02:42,360 --> 00:02:45,920
so instead, retroactively and in hindsight,

54
00:02:46,200 --> 00:02:48,920
I wave a white flag and the sea is calm with no waves.

55
00:02:50,200 --> 00:02:52,960
Pinchas makes sense.
You just don’t get him.

56
00:02:53,600 --> 00:02:55,120
I didn’t get it, but it sounds reasonable.

57
00:02:55,200 --> 00:02:57,840
Pinchas...
-Don’t you see I’m waving a white flag?

58
00:02:59,040 --> 00:03:01,760
Here, eat.
-Is it hot?

59
00:03:02,320 --> 00:03:04,960
Why with your hands, like a barbarian? Give him a plate.

60
00:03:05,040 --> 00:03:07,120
It tastes better with your hands, Mom.

61
00:03:07,200 --> 00:03:09,800
Yeah, one day you'll accidentally eat your own fingers.

62
00:03:09,880 --> 00:03:13,000
Mom, please, this isn't the time for that.
-How long have you been together?

63
00:03:13,080 --> 00:03:16,320
Seven weeks.
-Well, maybe you started by mistake.

64
00:03:16,400 --> 00:03:19,520
Those seven weeks were rough. Now it’ll be good.

65
00:03:19,640 --> 00:03:22,120
I really hope those were the bad seven weeks.

66
00:03:22,240 --> 00:03:26,960
Because if those were the good ones,
I don't want to imagine what's coming.

67
00:03:27,600 --> 00:03:30,640
Bad times with that troublemaker.
-What's a troublemaker?

68
00:03:30,800 --> 00:03:33,640
I already told you,
when couples fight, each one thinks

69
00:03:33,800 --> 00:03:35,080
their partner is the troublemaker.

70
00:03:35,560 --> 00:03:38,480
I'm sure your dad doesn't think I'm a troublemaker.

71
00:03:38,560 --> 00:03:41,760
Of course not! You're not a troublemaker.

72
00:03:42,320 --> 00:03:44,000
That's...
-A troublemaker is a guy! A Mizrahi?

73
00:03:44,840 --> 00:03:49,200
Compared to Yael, my wife, you're an angel.
-And how am I compared to Shai?

74
00:03:49,280 --> 00:03:53,080
What do you mean? What a question, what...
You're both angels.

75
00:03:53,640 --> 00:03:55,560
Yeah, but my Yael really was an angel.

76
00:03:58,240 --> 00:04:02,720
It's like this since three in the morning,
he goes "uhhh" every fifteen minutes.

77
00:04:03,120 --> 00:04:06,440
Oh, that's tough. How long will he be simmering at your place?

78
00:04:06,520 --> 00:04:08,840
Until they make up. I really hope
it won't take too long.

79
00:04:09,160 --> 00:04:10,760
Because if not, I'm kicking both of them out of the house.

80
00:04:10,880 --> 00:04:12,400
Or I'm moving in with Tzvi's wife.

81
00:04:13,000 --> 00:04:14,960
Shabbat Shalom.
-Shabbat Shalom.

82
00:04:15,040 --> 00:04:18,560
What, are you alone?
-I'm torn apart.

83
00:04:18,640 --> 00:04:21,519
Collecting chicken thighs all night. Is it any wonder he's tired during the day?

84
00:04:21,600 --> 00:04:22,960
Adam?
-Yeah, it's me.

85
00:04:23,040 --> 00:04:27,080
I thought I heard you.
-I'm just closing my eyes for five minutes. Okay?

86
00:04:27,160 --> 00:04:30,000
Don't you want some eggs?
-No, he's more into

87
00:04:30,080 --> 00:04:31,440
chicken thighs.
-Enough already.

88
00:04:32,000 --> 00:04:34,760
Riki never makes chicken thighs.
They're too juicy for her taste.

89
00:04:35,400 --> 00:04:39,120
Someone else might enjoy that.
-Pinchas, I can hear you.

90
00:04:39,760 --> 00:04:42,280
You want to switch to Shai and Shani for a week,

91
00:04:42,640 --> 00:04:46,840
so all the guys can complain together?
-Sorry, Riki, sorry.

92
00:04:46,920 --> 00:04:50,720
No, don't say "sorry,"
say "thank you for what I have."

93
00:04:50,800 --> 00:04:53,880
Because it can always be a lot worse.

94
00:04:53,960 --> 00:04:55,200
Thanks, Riki, thanks.

95
00:04:56,720 --> 00:05:00,480
You see, no matter what I do,
I always end up getting in trouble.

96
00:05:00,560 --> 00:05:02,400
You guys are just pretending to be victims.

97
00:05:02,880 --> 00:05:04,680
No, Shai, we're not pretending to be victims.

98
00:05:04,840 --> 00:05:07,880
We really are victims.
You women are oppressing us

99
00:05:07,960 --> 00:05:11,360
and then shout "equality."
I say: come on, I wish

100
00:05:11,440 --> 00:05:14,520
there was already equality.
We don't even have rights in our own home.

101
00:05:14,800 --> 00:05:17,000
Freedom fighter.

102
00:05:17,560 --> 00:05:18,960
Pinchas Luther King.

103
00:05:19,520 --> 00:05:22,800
Shai and...
,h chimibutzan
.
L'shon!

104
00:05:23,600 --> 00:05:25,560
Quiet! This is the living room.

105
00:05:26,640 --> 00:05:29,880
Ben, my brother, how do you feel after...

106
00:05:30,440 --> 00:05:34,560
Seven chicken thighs?
-It's filling but not uplifting.

107
00:05:34,840 --> 00:05:39,280
No, I told you it wouldn't help.
No worries, Adam just arrived,

108
00:05:39,680 --> 00:05:42,800
he'll tell you how nice it is in the single life,

109
00:05:43,080 --> 00:05:45,280
I'm sure it'll cheer you up.

110
00:05:45,360 --> 00:05:47,360
You won't believe the girls he meets.

111
00:05:47,680 --> 00:05:50,600
Yeah, but today he came alone. He's really tired.

112
00:05:50,880 --> 00:05:53,360
I think he had two night shifts.

113
00:05:54,880 --> 00:05:56,800
Come on, brother, come hear some stories. If he's lucky,

114
00:05:56,880 --> 00:05:57,920
he might flirt with a celebrity.

115
00:06:07,920 --> 00:06:11,840
What? They finished your chicken thighs.
-It's okay, may they enjoy them.

116
00:06:12,040 --> 00:06:14,000
Yeah, I would say "enjoy,"
but after what they did to me

117
00:06:14,160 --> 00:06:16,920
last night, that wasn't enjoyment,
it was a sickness.

118
00:06:17,000 --> 00:06:19,200
And then the maid comes in the morning and cries about everything.

119
00:06:19,280 --> 00:06:23,640
It'll pass. Tzvi and his wife will make up,
it'll end and he'll go back home.

120
00:06:24,200 --> 00:06:26,480
Amen!
-It was the same when Shai lived here.

121
00:06:26,560 --> 00:06:29,800
If he was in a fight with some girl
or if he was arguing with his parents.

122
00:06:29,880 --> 00:06:33,040
And he stayed to sleep.
-How long would that usually take?

123
00:06:33,120 --> 00:06:37,000
You know his dad is
the head cardiologist at Assaf Harofeh,

124
00:06:38,080 --> 00:06:42,680
if you ever need it.
-Why would I need it?

125
00:06:42,760 --> 00:06:47,640
Because you're an "I type person,"
you take things to heart and pound schnitzels.

126
00:06:48,280 --> 00:06:50,960
Thanks for the encouragement, Riki.
-Anytime, sweetie.

127
00:06:51,560 --> 00:06:54,800
Sit down, leave that alone,
don’t interfere with Shai and his friends.

128
00:06:54,880 --> 00:06:58,120
You’re not at risk, trust me.
I’m saying this for your own good.

129
00:06:58,960 --> 00:07:02,120
I don’t have the skills I developed anymore.

130
00:07:05,840 --> 00:07:08,120
Ahh, no.
-What happened? Did something happen?

131
00:07:09,080 --> 00:07:09,920
Nothing.

132
00:07:16,200 --> 00:07:19,480
Come on, Riki’s schnitzel helper?
-Not really.

133
00:07:19,640 --> 00:07:23,640
Wait, Dad, I thought Adam's stories
were still the same.

134
00:07:24,120 --> 00:07:29,360
Leave him alone, he’s tired.
-Adam, Adam, why are you so tired?

135
00:07:29,440 --> 00:07:33,280
Leave it, bro, let the kid be.
-Tell it, tell it, come on.

136
00:07:33,520 --> 00:07:36,680
I didn’t sleep all night, okay?
-He didn’t sleep all night. You get it?

137
00:07:36,760 --> 00:07:39,800
Leave him, leave him alone.
-Hey, Tzvi’s here, say hi.

138
00:07:40,640 --> 00:07:43,600
Hey, Tzvi, sorry, I’m just wiped out.
-It’s okay.

139
00:07:43,680 --> 00:07:46,080
No, wait, I promised him
a juicy story like that,

140
00:07:46,160 --> 00:07:48,520
to cheer him up.
-Sure, there are plenty of stories.

141
00:07:48,600 --> 00:07:50,720
Let him sleep.
-Alright, one story and I’m out.

142
00:07:50,880 --> 00:07:54,920
I promised a friend I’d tell him what’s
going on in the single life in Tel Aviv. Come on.

143
00:07:55,000 --> 00:07:57,920
You don’t know what he’s already been through.
-Leave them alone, enough.

144
00:07:58,000 --> 00:08:01,200
So why, why didn’t you sleep last night?
-Because someone dumped me. Okay?

145
00:08:02,400 --> 00:08:05,840
Someone I wanted. So I spent the whole night
sitting in some bar feeling sorry for myself. Okay?

146
00:08:10,000 --> 00:08:11,280
Yo.
Dad's going to sleep on the balcony.

147
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:20,360
Those whines...
-I didn’t remember it was this intense.

148
00:08:23,520 --> 00:08:24,480
Okay, I can’t take it anymore.

149
00:08:35,400 --> 00:08:39,760
Yael, Yael, Yael. Yael!

150
00:08:43,320 --> 00:08:45,920
Hey, Yael. No, it’s not Tzvi, it’s Shai’s Shabi.

151
00:08:46,040 --> 00:08:49,200
Listen, I really know it’s like this,
it’s not customary to interfere between couples,

152
00:08:49,280 --> 00:08:52,520
but Tzvi is just howling and whining like crazy.

153
00:08:53,080 --> 00:08:55,720
I’m sure you can forgive him
for some nonsense he didn’t do.

154
00:08:55,840 --> 00:08:57,000
No, he won’t do it again.

155
00:08:57,920 --> 00:09:00,240
Huh? Shabi.

156
00:09:01,480 --> 00:09:02,440
Shabi of Shai.

157
00:09:03,600 --> 00:09:05,040
Shai Rosen, his friend.

158
00:09:06,320 --> 00:09:07,360
Are you Yael?

159
00:09:08,200 --> 00:09:09,280
And you’re not his wife?

160
00:09:10,800 --> 00:09:14,560
Yael from work. Sorry, it’s a mistake.

161
00:09:15,680 --> 00:09:16,720
Whoa...

162
00:09:19,680 --> 00:09:20,880
I can’t stand this anymore.

163
00:09:21,520 --> 00:09:24,200
Honey? Honey.

164
00:09:29,440 --> 00:09:31,760
Hi. No, it’s not Tzvi. Yael?

165
00:09:33,520 --> 00:09:38,080
Honey. Ah, he...
I’m really sorry. I got confused.

166
00:09:38,280 --> 00:09:39,680
Sorry. What’s this?

167
00:09:40,640 --> 00:09:41,920
Yes, I can pass it to him.

168
00:09:42,800 --> 00:09:43,680
What?

169
00:09:44,640 --> 00:09:47,440
That they moved his appointment with the proctologist up by two days.

170
00:09:48,360 --> 00:09:50,560
Alright, I’ll let him know. Bye.

171
00:09:53,040 --> 00:09:55,080
You’ll really have a reason to whine soon.

172
00:09:56,360 --> 00:09:57,520
Mishmash?

173
00:09:58,160 --> 00:09:59,120
It’s probably his mom.

174
00:09:59,200 --> 00:10:01,000
Mom, you idiot. What are you doing here?

175
00:10:02,240 --> 00:10:05,640
I really don’t care what you’re doing.
I’m going to sleep in the bedroom.

176
00:10:06,200 --> 00:10:08,080
Call me for food.
-Oh! Babe.

177
00:10:08,840 --> 00:10:10,440
Thanks.
-Not you.

178
00:10:11,200 --> 00:10:12,360
Babe.

179
00:10:16,880 --> 00:10:19,160
Yael? It’s Shai’s Shabi.

180
00:10:20,680 --> 00:10:21,600
Yes, he’s here.

181
00:10:23,280 --> 00:10:26,880
I don't get it. What were you fighting about?
-I don't know. We were talking,

182
00:10:27,880 --> 00:10:31,400
and then suddenly she flipped out.
At first, words were thrown,

183
00:10:31,520 --> 00:10:35,160
then vases were thrown,
and I told her: if you don't calm down,

184
00:10:35,280 --> 00:10:37,320
I'm leaving the house for good.
-And...?

185
00:10:37,560 --> 00:10:40,600
He left for a day and a half.
-Maybe I was wrong.

186
00:10:41,800 --> 00:10:45,240
She was so young when we got married.
-No, no, no. Tzvi, Tzvi,

187
00:10:45,520 --> 00:10:47,040
Don't whine. Tzvi, no!

188
00:10:49,200 --> 00:10:51,120
What’s going on? What happened?
-What happened?

189
00:10:51,480 --> 00:10:55,040
Wow, Tzvi, what a story! 20 years.

190
00:10:55,120 --> 00:10:56,720
No, I'm dying. Can't you see he's crying?

191
00:10:58,840 --> 00:11:00,320
What happened to him?
-He fought with his wife.

192
00:11:00,400 --> 00:11:03,800
So he left the house! He slept at our place.
-Sorry to hear that.

193
00:11:03,880 --> 00:11:06,280
What, what happened?
-Do you really want to know?

194
00:11:06,360 --> 00:11:08,800
No, I'm just asking out of politeness.
-He's joking.

195
00:11:09,160 --> 00:11:10,000
I'm not.

196
00:11:10,640 --> 00:11:11,600
It's you guys.

197
00:11:11,680 --> 00:11:12,560
Oh, Riki.
-Oh, Mom.

198
00:11:12,640 --> 00:11:14,440
How's it going? Got schnitzel?
-Of course.

199
00:11:15,640 --> 00:11:17,760
You're building here today.
-Thanks.

200
00:11:17,840 --> 00:11:18,880
What happened?
-What?

201
00:11:18,960 --> 00:11:20,760
I'm in the kitchen.
-I'm coming.

202
00:11:20,840 --> 00:11:23,160
Maybe I'll go down to the car.
-Tell me, are you normal?

203
00:11:24,800 --> 00:11:26,720
You're not going to the kitchen to eat.
You're asking him what happened,

204
00:11:27,040 --> 00:11:27,920
with empathy.

205
00:11:30,720 --> 00:11:33,760
Me, Tzvi, what happened? Tell me.

206
00:11:33,920 --> 00:11:36,280
Itamar, do me a favor, go eat something.
Later, if you have the energy,

207
00:11:36,360 --> 00:11:38,360
come back for dessert, to hear gossip.
-Thank you very much.

208
00:11:38,760 --> 00:11:40,240
Tzvi, Tzvi, no! No!

209
00:11:44,320 --> 00:11:46,840
You avoided the living room because of Tzvi?
-Yeah.

210
00:11:47,320 --> 00:11:50,200
That Tzvi messed me up.
-Ahhh.

211
00:11:50,520 --> 00:11:51,400
Ahhh.
-Oh dear.

212
00:11:52,240 --> 00:11:54,160
Sorry, am I interrupting your quality time with my mom?

213
00:11:54,720 --> 00:11:57,560
Itamar, stop messing around and take some schnitzel,

214
00:11:57,640 --> 00:12:00,400
it'll make you stop talking nonsense.
-What do you want,

215
00:12:00,480 --> 00:12:03,880
Michal's been grinding my brain all day
that I'm rude and tactless,

216
00:12:03,960 --> 00:12:06,720
so I just checked—
-For a change, she was right.

217
00:12:07,640 --> 00:12:11,400
What? Did you meet Tzvi?
-I heard you opened a shelter for whiners?

218
00:12:11,960 --> 00:12:13,800
I'm coming too.
-What do you have to whine about?

219
00:12:13,880 --> 00:12:17,320
You had a golden wife. You didn't know how to keep her,

220
00:12:17,400 --> 00:12:18,880
she slipped through your fingers.
-What slipped?

221
00:12:18,960 --> 00:12:22,640
How can you hold an eel?
-Eat, eat.

222
00:12:23,200 --> 00:12:26,040
There's nothing to do with Tzvi.
-Actually, there is.

223
00:12:27,600 --> 00:12:30,160
I called his wife.
-You had her number?

224
00:12:30,360 --> 00:12:32,920
No, but I had his number.

225
00:12:34,360 --> 00:12:36,320
And what did you tell her?
-I told her the truth,

226
00:12:36,400 --> 00:12:39,280
that he regrets it, that he's crying,
that he's whining, that he asks for forgiveness

227
00:12:39,360 --> 00:12:40,920
and that he's waiting for her to come get him.

228
00:12:41,280 --> 00:12:44,640
Did he ask you to do that?
-Not exactly, but he hinted.

229
00:12:45,200 --> 00:12:48,480
He forgot his phone next to me.
-Nice.

230
00:12:48,680 --> 00:12:50,360
Good job, I never liked that Tzvi.

231
00:12:50,440 --> 00:12:52,600
He and Shai always bullied me
when I was a little kid.

232
00:12:52,680 --> 00:12:54,680
Itamar, please. Don't talk with your mouth full.

233
00:12:54,760 --> 00:12:56,400
What’s with all of you today?

234
00:12:56,680 --> 00:12:58,280
I didn't know you had that in you.

235
00:12:59,760 --> 00:13:01,120
What, is that a compliment, Riki?

236
00:13:02,480 --> 00:13:04,560
Because I don't know whether to be happy.
-Be happy, be happy.

237
00:13:04,640 --> 00:13:07,560
Because that's the closest to a compliment I've ever heard
my mom say to anyone.

238
00:13:07,880 --> 00:13:11,160
That's really something.
More than that, it would be a Nobel Prize

239
00:13:11,240 --> 00:13:12,520
or lighting the torch.

240
00:13:14,240 --> 00:13:15,440
Suck in your stomach.

241
00:13:17,200 --> 00:13:19,440
Tzvi, do you want to watch something on TV?

242
00:13:19,520 --> 00:13:21,800
There's a new show by Aharoni, you haven't seen anything like it.

243
00:13:22,000 --> 00:13:24,880
I'm still full from the schnitzels.
-What did he do to his wife?

244
00:13:24,960 --> 00:13:28,680
Why do you jump to conclusions?
-Because I don't understand what he's doing here.

245
00:13:28,760 --> 00:13:31,480
Like talking to his wife, for example.
-I never want to talk to her again.

246
00:13:32,600 --> 00:13:33,440
Come on
Come here.

247
00:13:35,640 --> 00:13:37,680
Yael, what are you doing here? How did you know I was here?

248
00:13:37,760 --> 00:13:41,120
What do you mean how did I know?
You asked Shabi to call me, right?

249
00:13:41,200 --> 00:13:42,880
-No. Shabi.

250
00:13:42,960 --> 00:13:46,040
Shabi called you?
-Yeah, she said you wanted to make up.

251
00:13:46,120 --> 00:13:48,240
And that I should come.
-I don't want to handle our fights.

252
00:13:48,320 --> 00:13:51,080
Here in front of everyone.
-You can go to the bedroom.

253
00:13:51,160 --> 00:13:52,640
Ignore the mess.
-Thanks.

254
00:13:52,920 --> 00:13:54,680
What are you doing here?
-What do you mean "what am I doing here"?

255
00:13:56,760 --> 00:13:58,120
Sit down, babe...
-What?

256
00:13:58,200 --> 00:14:01,160
What did you do? Did you call Yael?
-Yeah. Did she arrive? Is she here?

257
00:14:01,240 --> 00:14:03,080
Yeah, they're in the bedroom.
-Oh, great, great.

258
00:14:03,640 --> 00:14:05,960
You can't just do things like that without talking to me,

259
00:14:06,040 --> 00:14:07,800
he's your friend, you just complicated things for them.

260
00:14:07,920 --> 00:14:11,200
Shai, don't make a big deal out of it.
-Mom, this is between me and my wife.

261
00:14:11,280 --> 00:14:16,040
They'll talk and make up.
She actually handled it just fine this time.

262
00:14:16,120 --> 00:14:20,760
Riki, it's their business.
You don't have to interfere in everything.

263
00:14:20,840 --> 00:14:22,720
You always interfere and I hold back
from saying anything to you,

264
00:14:22,800 --> 00:14:24,680
but this time you crossed the line.

265
00:14:24,760 --> 00:14:27,000
Pinchas, since when do you interfere?

266
00:14:27,120 --> 00:14:31,400
Since when do you call me out in front of everyone?
-See what you did now?

267
00:14:31,480 --> 00:14:32,560
Instead of one fight, there are now three fights.

268
00:14:32,640 --> 00:14:34,360
Enough, come on, babe. I had good intentions.

269
00:14:34,440 --> 00:14:36,200
Yeah, good intentions on the way to hell?

270
00:14:36,280 --> 00:14:40,240
Okay, Pinchas, apologize and let's end this.
-Enough! Stop!

271
00:14:40,840 --> 00:14:43,400
You shouldn't have interfered
in the argument between Shai and Shani.

272
00:14:43,520 --> 00:14:45,080
About whether she should have interfered or not.

273
00:14:45,320 --> 00:14:49,520
Why? Sometimes it's a mitzvah to interfere.
-Why do you think you know everything?

274
00:14:49,680 --> 00:14:53,800
Do you even know what happened between Tzvi
and Yael that made it right to call them?

275
00:14:53,880 --> 00:14:57,320
I'll say what I think.
She got married very young,

276
00:14:57,720 --> 00:15:01,280
so either she's naive or she's after money.

277
00:15:01,360 --> 00:15:04,320
What?
-Mom, Michal's here, that's not nice.

278
00:15:04,440 --> 00:15:06,520
Is that all you have to say to her, "Michal's here"?

279
00:15:06,840 --> 00:15:09,320
You might be really old,
but you're just a four-year-old kid.

280
00:15:09,880 --> 00:15:12,000
What are you saying? Three fights plus one for free.

281
00:15:12,200 --> 00:15:14,880
It's not her fault. It's Pinchas.

282
00:15:14,960 --> 00:15:17,840
No, it's not Dad, it's Michal
who suddenly snapped at me.

283
00:15:18,840 --> 00:15:20,440
Come on, you see this has nothing to do with me?

284
00:15:22,200 --> 00:15:24,640
Tell me, are you normal? What are you doing here?
Do you want to act out here too

285
00:15:24,720 --> 00:15:26,320
and throw vases?
-You're an idiot.

286
00:15:27,040 --> 00:15:29,040
Ouch!
-Sorry.

287
00:15:32,640 --> 00:15:33,760
Sorry, just a second.

288
00:15:39,080 --> 00:15:39,960
What are you doing here?

289
00:15:40,200 --> 00:15:43,640
I told you, Shabi called from your phone,
said you wanted to make up

290
00:15:43,920 --> 00:15:45,920
and that I should come. But what does it matter?

291
00:15:46,040 --> 00:15:47,600
Do you want to talk or not?
-But why here?

292
00:15:47,840 --> 00:15:49,440
We're already here, right?
-But we can't talk here.

293
00:15:49,520 --> 00:15:51,960
Do you want me to leave?
-People are listening.

294
00:15:52,400 --> 00:15:55,120
So you'll have to talk quietly
and I'll manage without the vases.

295
00:15:55,200 --> 00:15:57,880
No, I don't get you. You took his
phone and snooped through the numbers?

296
00:15:57,960 --> 00:16:00,400
A phone is personal.
-Come on, I'm really interested in the phone numbers

297
00:16:00,480 --> 00:16:02,560
on Tzvi's phone. I was looking for
Yael's number, his wife.

298
00:16:02,640 --> 00:16:04,640
Okay, but how can you do something like that
without talking to me?

299
00:16:04,720 --> 00:16:07,680
Come on, what? Now maybe I need to
ask you for permission to breathe?

300
00:16:07,760 --> 00:16:10,240
Okay, I'm asking you to promise me
that you'll never do things like this.

301
00:16:10,320 --> 00:16:11,720
You're getting involved with my friends on your own.

302
00:16:11,960 --> 00:16:17,080
Shai, Tzvi is a friend of both of ours.
And if he feels comfortable hanging out all night,

303
00:16:17,200 --> 00:16:19,680
and using my kitchen without a care,

304
00:16:19,760 --> 00:16:22,200
then I don't count him or you at all.

305
00:16:22,280 --> 00:16:25,400
Riki, this can't go on like this.
You're always interfering in their lives.

306
00:16:25,480 --> 00:16:27,720
Are you raising a black flag?
-No,

307
00:16:27,920 --> 00:16:30,880
but this is already an invasion of their privacy, for crying out loud.

308
00:16:30,960 --> 00:16:35,720
You don't get it, this is the modern world,
it's okay to interfere.

309
00:16:35,800 --> 00:16:40,720
This generation has no secrets
or privacy. That's just how it is.

310
00:16:40,800 --> 00:16:45,000
Everything is open on the internet, on Facebook.
Everything is transparent and visible.

311
00:16:45,960 --> 00:16:49,760
You know what they say? Those who live in glass houses

312
00:16:50,000 --> 00:16:53,800
shouldn't walk around naked. If you hadn't called me out,

313
00:16:54,400 --> 00:16:57,560
it wouldn't have escalated into a bigger fight.
-But how long can I stay quiet?

314
00:16:57,760 --> 00:17:00,560
You keep silencing me and in the end...
-Here, take a schnitzel.

315
00:17:02,440 --> 00:17:05,040
Do you realize that even your picture here
is from your wedding with Smadar?

316
00:17:05,760 --> 00:17:08,880
Babe, that's a great picture of me
and I'm alone here, Smadar isn't here.

317
00:17:08,960 --> 00:17:11,800
That's my mom who put it there.
-Does it bother you that I'm not here

318
00:17:12,079 --> 00:17:14,079
or that your mom thinks
I'm with you because I'm after your money?

319
00:17:14,160 --> 00:17:16,640
Come on, babe, I don't want to fight.
-You're acting like a little kid.

320
00:17:16,760 --> 00:17:18,480
Said the little girl.
-They called! From the daycare,

321
00:17:18,599 --> 00:17:20,440
they said you forgot a pacifier.
-Okay, come on, come on, come on.

322
00:17:20,560 --> 00:17:23,160
Go back to the nursery you crawled out of.
-Is this a grown-up argument for you?

323
00:17:23,319 --> 00:17:25,720
I thought we were lowering ourselves to your level.
-No, we're lowering to your level...

324
00:17:27,440 --> 00:17:30,000
Go eat mashed baba.
-Idiot.

325
00:17:30,640 --> 00:17:34,160
And how we laughed at your dumb sister-in-law.
-Dumb?

326
00:17:34,320 --> 00:17:37,240
At least she's not as dumb as your Aunt Amalia.

327
00:17:38,040 --> 00:17:39,200
Amalia's not dumb.

328
00:17:40,680 --> 00:17:41,560
It's something you're born with.

329
00:17:44,080 --> 00:17:47,000
You know, overall we're good together.
It's not as bad as it seems.

330
00:17:47,240 --> 00:17:49,240
True.
-I'm crazy about you.

331
00:17:49,480 --> 00:17:52,600
And I'm crazy about you. Okay, we need to fight a bit. Right?

332
00:17:53,360 --> 00:17:54,800
Every sea needs a few waves.

333
00:17:55,440 --> 00:17:56,600
It's good for the surfers.

334
00:17:57,080 --> 00:18:00,440
It's a principle. Because even if we're a couple,
everyone decides on their own friends.

335
00:18:00,520 --> 00:18:03,520
Tell me, don't you understand that when you
give him shelter, you're no longer a friend,

336
00:18:03,600 --> 00:18:05,640
because then he knows he has somewhere to escape
and takes advantage of it

337
00:18:05,720 --> 00:18:08,000
instead of going and confronting his wife.
What kind of friend are you?

338
00:18:08,080 --> 00:18:11,480
One who opens the door when someone knocks.
And if he needs a shoulder, he gives...

339
00:18:11,600 --> 00:18:14,920
He gives everything.
Forget it, the last image didn't work for me

340
00:18:15,040 --> 00:18:17,360
but you get the idea.
-For you, it's fine if he doesn't go home,

341
00:18:17,480 --> 00:18:20,920
right? Cool for you, let them hang out all night,
laugh, whine together,

342
00:18:21,040 --> 00:18:23,640
gossip about me. Why not?
-Shai, enough, enough. Really, I love you,

343
00:18:23,720 --> 00:18:26,480
I love you. Let's not fight, okay?
I think you shouldn't have interfered,

344
00:18:26,560 --> 00:18:29,640
you think differently...
-I can't take it, I don't want to hear you anymore.

345
00:18:29,720 --> 00:18:31,960
Don't you notice how you
keep hurting me in front of everyone?

346
00:18:32,080 --> 00:18:34,160
If you don't want to be with me, Itamar,
then don't be with me.

347
00:18:34,240 --> 00:18:36,120
Tell me, what happened, did you change tactics?
Did you switch to whining?

348
00:18:36,200 --> 00:18:38,800
I'm not whining at all, I'm just
saying maybe your mom is right,

349
00:18:38,880 --> 00:18:40,600
maybe it's better if you really go back to Smadar
because she's much more mature

350
00:18:40,720 --> 00:18:42,160
!she gets along with mom way better
-Okay, babe...

351
00:18:42,240 --> 00:18:43,240
Don't call me babe!

352
00:18:45,760 --> 00:18:46,760
Am I interrupting?

353
00:18:46,840 --> 00:18:47,800
We're in the middle of a fight.

354
00:18:49,760 --> 00:18:51,720
Sorry, I have nowhere else to be.
-Did something happen?

355
00:18:51,800 --> 00:18:52,640
Okay, leave her alone.

356
00:18:52,720 --> 00:18:54,280
Let's go continue somewhere else.
-I'm done.

357
00:18:54,360 --> 00:18:55,480
I'm not!
-I am!

358
00:18:56,680 --> 00:18:59,200
What, you're not leaving me in the middle of a fight.
Itamar, come here!

359
00:18:59,440 --> 00:19:01,640
Itamar, come here! Itamar!

360
00:19:01,720 --> 00:19:04,480
So you're saying you usually stay quiet and don't respond?

361
00:19:04,560 --> 00:19:07,560
Yeah, because I choose not to fight with you.

362
00:19:07,640 --> 00:19:10,960
So why this time?
-Because this time you went too far.

363
00:19:11,600 --> 00:19:15,040
Alright, fine, I won't interfere anymore.
-Thanks, Riki.

364
00:19:15,560 --> 00:19:19,040
Turns out she called his wife
not to make peace between them,

365
00:19:19,120 --> 00:19:22,800
but for her own personal interest
which is that he won't be at our house anymore.

366
00:19:22,920 --> 00:19:26,560
Shai, there's no such thing as no interests.

367
00:19:26,840 --> 00:19:30,680
If you pay attention, you'll see that everything Shani does

368
00:19:31,000 --> 00:19:33,520
is out of self-interest.
-You're interfering again.

369
00:19:33,600 --> 00:19:36,240
Pinchas, enough with that!
-I'm fed up.

370
00:19:36,440 --> 00:19:38,880
Fine, you don't have to. Go find something else to do.

371
00:19:43,080 --> 00:19:44,840
How rude!
-What nonsense!

372
00:19:46,560 --> 00:19:48,880
Do you really think it's okay to involve
my mom in every argument we have?

373
00:19:48,960 --> 00:19:51,560
Look at that. When it comes to your mom
suddenly you lose your tact.

374
00:19:51,720 --> 00:19:52,840
And why do you need to involve...

375
00:19:56,640 --> 00:19:57,640
Excuse me for a second.

376
00:20:02,400 --> 00:20:04,560
Why do you need to involve Smadar in every argument?

377
00:20:04,640 --> 00:20:07,480
Smadar the saint.
-She's my ex-wife.

378
00:20:07,560 --> 00:20:10,800
Maybe she'll be your future wife too.
-Just so you know, you're starting to annoy me

379
00:20:10,880 --> 00:20:12,560
Level nine on the Itamar scale.

380
00:20:12,640 --> 00:20:14,440
Oh, yeah, maybe you should get down from the scale
you climbed, Itamar,

381
00:20:14,520 --> 00:20:16,560
and look at me a bit and see how much you're hurting me.

382
00:20:16,760 --> 00:20:18,720
Like, do you even love me?

383
00:20:21,480 --> 00:20:22,600
Mom!

384
00:20:23,480 --> 00:20:26,320
What?
-Look, she's interfering again.

385
00:20:27,880 --> 00:20:31,040
No, we can't do this here. Come on.
-What a shame.

386
00:20:32,120 --> 00:20:34,240
At least you're as happy as I am?
-At least our happiness

387
00:20:34,320 --> 00:20:35,880
doesn't come at the expense of others.

388
00:20:36,640 --> 00:20:38,440
How rude!
-What nonsense!

389
00:20:38,520 --> 00:20:40,160
I'm dying.
-Unbelievable.

390
00:20:40,640 --> 00:20:44,480
Who needs this babysitter?
-No one can tell me in my own house not to interfere.

391
00:20:44,960 --> 00:20:47,000
See you later.
-Thanks for everything.

392
00:20:47,280 --> 00:20:50,720
Bro, I'll talk to you tomorrow. Thanks, Pinchas.

393
00:20:51,200 --> 00:20:52,120
Bye.

394
00:20:54,160 --> 00:20:56,600
Ben, you see? They left on good terms.

395
00:20:57,200 --> 00:21:00,000
Yeah, look at that, Riki.
They managed to get along and make up.

396
00:21:00,080 --> 00:21:01,320
Great, because I'm starving.

397
00:21:02,000 --> 00:21:06,720
Babe, I'm sorry if I said
a word here and there that I shouldn't have,

398
00:21:07,200 --> 00:21:11,480
sorry, and I love you a lot.
-How much is a lot?

399
00:21:12,080 --> 00:21:13,800
There are no words to describe how much.

400
00:21:13,880 --> 00:21:15,560
Babe.

401
00:21:16,480 --> 00:21:19,240
You see, Pinchas, sometimes you need to interfere.

402
00:21:19,480 --> 00:21:22,840
It's not always right to stand on the sidelines.
-Okay, I get it.

403
00:21:23,080 --> 00:21:26,840
Sorry, you're right, I'm an idiot.
-Just like your son, he turned out to be an idiot too.

404
00:21:26,920 --> 00:21:28,160
I'm sorry.

405
00:21:28,240 --> 00:21:32,480
Oh, all the men apologized. Let's sit down to eat.

406
00:21:43,040 --> 00:21:44,960
How did you manage to fight again?
-I don't know, we left your mom's,

407
00:21:45,040 --> 00:21:46,800
got in the car, and suddenly we started fighting.

408
00:21:46,880 --> 00:21:49,840
That's exactly when we made up.
-No, I just can't believe it.

409
00:21:49,920 --> 00:21:52,240
I'm not going home. Permanently.
-You want to come to our place.

410
00:21:52,320 --> 00:21:53,520
Yeah.
-No, no, no.

411
00:21:53,640 --> 00:21:56,960
The whole house is exhausted,
at least give us one night without your...

412
00:21:58,120 --> 00:22:00,520
that.
-What, is it really bothering you? Huh?

413
00:22:00,680 --> 00:22:02,520
Not really.
-But yes. Yes.

414
00:22:02,880 --> 00:22:04,560
You want, I can take you
to a hotel nearby?

415
00:22:04,720 --> 00:22:06,920
No, no, no, no. Just drop me off at home,

416
00:22:07,000 --> 00:22:08,640
I'll try to sort this out with her.
-Great.

417
00:22:08,720 --> 00:22:10,240
It's also cheaper.
-Of course.

418
00:22:22,720 --> 00:22:25,400
Don't be a man, no, be a man,

419
00:22:25,960 --> 00:22:26,920
don't be a sucker.

420
00:22:28,000 --> 00:22:29,920
It's okay, bro, the birthday was next month.

421
00:22:31,160 --> 00:22:32,440
Last month.

422
00:22:33,280 --> 00:22:34,120
Which month?

423
00:22:35,360 --> 00:22:36,680
I don’t get it, what were you even fighting about?
-No.

424
00:22:37,640 --> 00:22:38,480
...Sorry.

425
00:22:38,960 --> 00:22:40,200
Go eat some porridge,

426
00:22:40,640 --> 00:22:42,200
Go eat a mashed banana!

427
00:22:42,920 --> 00:22:45,160
Go eat something you can have without teeth!

428
00:22:45,800 --> 00:22:46,640
Porridge?

429
00:22:47,680 --> 00:22:49,640
There's nothing to be done, Dad! The color is too bright.

430
00:22:50,240 --> 00:22:52,840
Why, Riki, specifically about this?

431
00:22:53,920 --> 00:22:56,480
I’ll tell you exactly what I pushed.

432
00:22:56,800 --> 00:23:00,800
She married him at a very young age, very young.

